<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870212-0005 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business:Macmillan Inc.</HL><DD> 02/12/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MLLBOND MARKET NEWS (BON) </IN><TEXT>   MACMILLAN INC., a New York-based publishing and printing concern, sold $125 million of 5 1/2% debentures priced at par and due Feb. 15, 2012, said Goldman, Sachs andamp; Co., lead underwriter. The securities are convertible at a rate of $69 of debentures for each common share. Proceeds will be used for general purposes, including future acquisitions, and may be used to repay borrowings incurred to finance last year's acquisitions. In composite trading on the New York Stock Exchange yesterday, the company's common shares closed at $53.625, down 50 cents. </TEXT></DOC>